21/02/2008
ROME, Italy -- Police in Verona on Wednesday (February 20th) arrested Serbian Sreten Pesalic, who was tried in absentia by a Croatian court and sentenced in 2002 to ten years in prison for war crimes. Pesalic, 38, lived in Verona, where he worked as a driver. He is charged with belonging to a Serb paramilitary group that tortured Croatians during the 1991 war and forced them to flee their homes. Pesalic was detained based on an international arrest warrant. (RTRS, SRNA, AFP, Tanjug, B92, Vecernji List - 20/02/08)
